The paper deals with the use of deepfake technology for de-identification of medical videos while preserving diagnostic information. This involves computer vision techniques for face and body keypoints detection, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also addresses ethical concerns related to privacy protection, which could be classified under human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the use of deepfake technology raises security concerns, which could be classified under cybersecurity (cs.CR). The paper also involves quantitative analysis of the effectiveness of the proposed method, which could be classified under machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with medical data sharing, which could be classified under multimedia (cs.MM).
